vectorData.altText: Identify the layer indicated by the letter A. Be specific.

Limited mitosis may occur here.
Keratin intermediate filaments bundle together to strengthen intercellular adhesion via desmosomes. 
Keratinocytes start to produce keratohyalin granules on their free ribosomes, which consist of intermediate filament-associated proteins. Membrane-bound lamellar granules, containing pro-barrier lipids, begin to form on RER.

Arises from cells in the s. spinosum. It is the second most common form of skin cancer that is more likely to metastasize, as compared to basal cell carcinoma.
The probable etiology is UV radiation; also x-radiation, chemical carcinogens.

That's right! Stratum spinosum is the layer between S. granulosum and S. basale. Under high magnification, keratinocytes in this layer appear spiny due to shrinkage of microfilaments between desmosomes.
